column5: Anyone know of a supplier of lure parts in Ontario other than Real Pro's? Rollie and Helens don't have what I need. And Moores Lures is leaving for the cottage for 2 weeks. I'm looking for #5,7,8 and 10 colorado blades....Any ideas?
Jef are you heading my way soon? if so I might be able to help you out through Janns Net craft they dont have #10 but so have the others.
Don't know how fast you need the parts Jeff, but possibly:  http://www.lindylittlejoe.com/  http://www.jannsnetcraft.com/  I was gonna suggest luremaking.com until I saw that RealPro's owns them,
THX Mike. No plans for westbound trips anytime soon.
Jeff give these guys a try.  http://www.upnorthoutdoors.com/stamina/spi...ner_blades.html
I make my own worm harness's, and I get all my stuff including all size's of blades at  Bass Pro! Scooter
